    <header class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <a class="back-link" href="../index.html">Back to Monty's archive</a>
        <h1>Gloria “Baby Gloria”</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          The youngest Montgomery treats society columns like playgrounds, effortlessly modelling the family brand
          before mastering cursive.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="cards-grid expanded-grid" aria-label="Baby Gloria details">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Miniature Wardrobe</h2>
            <p>
              Her closet is catalogued like a museum, complete with provenance cards and scheduled loan periods for photo
              shoots.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Media Training</h2>
            <p>
              Baby Gloria’s tutor doubles as a publicist, rehearsing phrases like “philanthropy playtime” before every
              appearance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Signature Causes</h2>
            <p>
              She promotes “Libraries for Littles,” a program donating gilded storybooks to hospital waiting rooms—with a
              custom monogram stamped inside each cover.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="page-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <p>Expanded archive entry for Gloria Montgomery.</p>
      </div>
